text: Tarcenay-Foucherans is a commune in the Doubs department in the Bourgogne- Franche-Comté region in eastern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Tarcenay (the seat) and Foucherans.Arrêté préfectoral 26 September 2018 ==See also== * Communes of the Doubs department ==References== Category:Communes of Doubs
title: Tarcenay-Foucherans
